dct_title_s: Extracts from the Chinese map of the Upper Oxus
dct_description_sm: Title given by cataloger. Shaded areas indicate deranged [inaccurate] portions of original map. Rivers, lakes, and settlements are shown. Shows longitude west from Peking [Beijing] and east from Greenwich. From: Journal of the Royal Geographical Society of London. Vol. 42 (1872), pp. 438-513; held in Firestone Library. Call number: G7 .J687 v.42 1872
dct_publisher_sm: London : published for the Journal of the Royal Geographical Society, by J. Murray, Albemarle Street, 1872.
